1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,120
[Congrats on graduation, Ah Hun.]
[Kang Ah Hun, You're An Adult Now!]

2
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,500
How can you call this a party?

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,900
This is a fight...

4
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:18,600
- Is it just coincident, Ji Hyeon Ho?
- Is it just coincident, Do Ye Seok?

5
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:21,170
- Beat him, Ji Hyeon Ho!
- Beat him, Do Ye Seok!

6
00:00:21,170 --> 00:00:23,600
- Go for it, Ji Hyeon Ho!
- Go for it, Do Ye Seok!

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:27,010
- Beat him, Ji Hyeon Ho!
- Beat him, Do Ye Seok!

8
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:36,600
I liked someone I shouldn't like.

9
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:42,200
Never.

10
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,700
Never?

11
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:49,400
She's not someone I shouldn't like.

12
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:06,300
I've regretted letting go of someone I like.

13
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,200
Never.

14
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:18,800
I get that you're competitive, but you shouldn't lie.

15
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,800
I never let her go,

16
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:24,900
so I have no regrets.

17
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:28,700
I mean... Why are they being so serious?

18
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:32,200
Why would they do their best in something useless like this?

19
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,600
What do you mean useless?

20
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:38,200
This is about men's pride.

21
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,200
I get it, too.

22
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,830
Even when we play baseball, it's really annoying if we lose.

23
00:01:42,830 --> 00:01:44,000
Right, right.

24
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Now, who is next?

25
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:49,980
Moving your position is cheating...

26
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:54,000
But, well, sometimes

27
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,400
cheating is necessary, so...

28
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,800
Let's sit.

29
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,600
I thought you were here to celebrate Ah Hun and me, Ji Seong, finishing SATs,

30
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,200
but they're just having fun on their own.

31
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,600
I'm bored.

32
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,600
Ji Seong, are you bored?

33
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:19,100
Then shall we play it, too?

34
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:21,000
Hey, don't pile it on.

35
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,200
Why not?

36
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:26,500
Those two won't stop until Yeon Du comes.

37
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:29,000
I'll call her to see where she is.

38
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,800
Squirtle!

39
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,500
Yeon Du!

40
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,900
I thought you weren't coming.

41
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:43,900
Sorry, I had to stop by the school.

42
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:46,300
It's okay. We totally understand.

43
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,400
Hurry and sit.

44
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,100
There is a seat next to your boyfriend.

45
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,600
[Best Mistake]

46
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:05,870
[Six months ago]
[2021-2 Year Department of Business Administration Class Opening Assembly]

47
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:08,310
- It's exciting.
- Who did it? Good job.

48
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:10,500
Have a drink.

49
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,800
Now!

50
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,200
We'll begin

51
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:18,900
the welcome party for Hwayang University's Department of Business Administration!

52
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:32,200
Okay, everyone, fill up your glasses.

53
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:36,000
Let's make an awesome toast.

54
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:40,060
Cheers for me, Kim Dae Yeong, and my fateful love.

55
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:42,960
- No, what is that?
- That was not on the agenda.

56
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:48,000
When he said "fateful love," it reminds me of Ji Seong.

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,400
He said he was going to find Wang Yingling, so Hyeon Ho had to...

58
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,900
What am I thinking?

59
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,400
It's all in the past.

60
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,800
I mean...

61
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:11,500
Am I not supposed to think about the past at all?

62
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:16,400
It's not a crime, right?

63
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:18,000
I said,

64
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:24,000
I want to think about Hyeon Ho with my own head.

65
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,400
And it's none of your business

66
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:31,100
None of your business!

67
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:34,100
Why aren't you saying anything?

68
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:36,800
Are you listening to me?

69
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,400
My head hurts...

70
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:44,600
I should go get some fresh air.

71
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,100
You wait right here.

72
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:52,400
And don't go anywhere.

73
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,400
Stay here.

74
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,200
I feel like my head's going to split.

75
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:10,600
You don't need to deal with it.

76
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,700
What the...

77
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,600
I'm sorry.

78
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:18,100
Hey, just saying sorry is not enough.

79
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:20,800
I'm sorry.

80
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:24,000
I said I'm sorry.

81
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,300
What?

82
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,300
What did you just say?

83
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:29,200
What did you just say?

84
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:31,000
Hey!

85
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,400
What time is it now?

86
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,300
What happened yesterday?

87
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:09,600
I got a bit drunk at the welcome party yesterday.

88
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,700
Well, a little more drunk than usual.

89
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,300
But it's not a crime.

90
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:17,200
It's none of your business!

91
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,900
And then...

92
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,700
Did I go outside?

93
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,500
Yes, right.

94
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:25,000
I went outside and bumped into someone.

95
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:27,800
Oh, I don't know.

96
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,700
At least I came home safely...

97
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,000
I don't know about safely...

98
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,300
But at least I came home.

99
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:38,090
I'm sure nothing bad happened.

100
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,560
- Is this a full tone?
- Yes.

101
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,080
Then try this one.

102
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:45,590
It's rather nice.

103
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:52,500
Seol, you look so good in that lip color.

104
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,500
It's a perfect color for you.

105
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,700
Hey, Yu Seol's makeup techniques have gotten so much better

106
00:06:57,700 --> 00:06:59,400
ever since she became a college student.

107
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,274
It's not that my technique is getting better.

108
00:07:01,274 --> 00:07:02,900
It's just that this company's products are great.

109
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:04,000
Really?

110
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,400
Really.

111
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,100
I've been using this for some time now.

112
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,300
This is the most popular one.

113
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,067
It has such a nice color.

114
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:13,089
And this, I'm wearing this right now.

115
00:07:13,089 --> 00:07:16,183
I bought it because it just came out, and the texture is amazing.

116
00:07:16,183 --> 00:07:18,658
But it has a pretty funny name.

117
00:07:18,658 --> 00:07:21,000
Kim Yeo Ju Gathering?

118
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,506
That's cute.

119
00:07:22,506 --> 00:07:25,717
- Ah Ra, do you want to try it?
- Yes.

120
00:07:25,717 --> 00:07:28,300
Oh, I love the color.

121
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,700
And the color comes out so well.

122
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,600
Seol, do you also use all these shadows?

123
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:36,392
- Yes.
- Thanks for the tip.

124
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:40,434
This is why I love being a college student.

125
00:07:40,434 --> 00:07:43,500
High school students are in school at this hour.

126
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,275
But I liked it when we were in high school.

127
00:07:46,275 --> 00:07:47,500
It was so much fun.

128
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,800
Fun?

129
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,700
Not that I had fun bullying Yeon Du...

130
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:55,300
I apologized to her, and she forgave me.

131
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,700
So please forget about it.

132
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:02,075
Anyway, now you're drinking coffee with us like this.

133
00:08:02,075 --> 00:08:04,100
So what was so fun about it?

134
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,312
You know,

135
00:08:05,337 --> 00:08:08,000
even if we were in different classes, we still hung out together.

136
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,551
But now we're in different schools, so we barely meet up.

137
00:08:10,551 --> 00:08:12,237
But still...

138
00:08:12,237 --> 00:08:15,500
Yeon Du and I are in the same school, and you and Yu Na are in the same school.

139
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,900
At least we have that.

140
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:19,014
Most of the time, friends all go to different schools.

141
00:08:19,014 --> 00:08:22,400
Hey, I never thought that you would be attending

142
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,800
the same school as Yeon Du.

143
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:27,600
You entered so many drawing contests in your senior year.

144
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:32,100
Who knew you'd enter a prestigious college as a student with special talents.

145
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,800
I'm so jealous.

146
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:35,375
But Yu Na,

147
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:38,052
- you have Seung Hyeon.
- That's right.

148
00:08:38,052 --> 00:08:39,547
Choi Seung Hyeon?

149
00:08:39,547 --> 00:08:41,237
It's just a crush now.

150
00:08:41,237 --> 00:08:43,900
But I'm going to make him mine soon.

151
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,600
You wait and see.

152
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,000
I'm jealous.

153
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,100
What?

154
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:51,200
I thought you and Jeong Ji Seong were an item.

155
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:55,300
Ji Seong has no idea that I like him.

156
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:58,800
I want to ask him out, but I don't want to bother his studies.

157
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:02,500
I'll have to wait until he takes the SAT.

158
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,375
That's true.

159
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:09,300
Just think of it as a punishment for not realizing how you felt sooner and hang in there.

160
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,800
Those are some champagne problems.

161
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:18,300
At least you guys can meet them whenever you want and talk to them face to face.

162
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:23,097
I can only see him through photos.

163
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,800
Yeon Du is here.

164
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,400
Hi!

165
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:41,300
Sorry, I'm late.

166
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:44,500
I got wasted at the welcome party yesterday.

167
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,100
Welcome party?

168
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:47,300
I thought you weren't going.

169
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:50,194
You said you were going on a date with Ji Hyeon Ho.

170
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,600
That's...

171
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,800
Your date!

172
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:58,000
Did you have fun? How was it?

173
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,100
What did you do? You two haven't met in a while.

174
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,400
In two weeks, right?

175
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,839
You must have had a great time since it's been a while.

176
00:10:06,839 --> 00:10:10,600
Ji Hyeon Ho must have turned into a romanticist, huh?

177
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,900
When did this cafe open?

178
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:15,575
It's really pretty, right?

179
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,933
We haven't seen each other for so long.

180
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:18,900
I know.

181
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:23,400
That cranky boy turns into such a romanticist in front of Yeon Du.

182
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,600
And he started dating like an adult after going to college.

183
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,000
I know.

184
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,100
He's always grumpy in front of us.

185
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,500
Excuse me,

186
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:36,506
- Hyeon Ho.
- I know.

187
00:10:36,506 --> 00:10:37,700
Take a photo.

188
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,600
You always take photos before you eat.

189
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,800
Do you remember we went out to eat last time?

190
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:45,900
He didn't even let us touch the food so Yeon Du could take pictures.

191
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:49,000
Now I know what to do even before you say it, right?

192
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,900
What are you waiting for?

193
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,600
Even the lighting is pretty, so the photos will come out nicely.

194
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:02,000
- Hyeon Ho.
- Yes?

195
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,000
We should...

196
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:09,100
So what did you two do yesterday?

197
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:11,975
Yes, tell us what happened.

198
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,975
I broke up with Hyeon Ho.

199
00:11:18,975 --> 00:11:20,939
- What?
- What?

200
00:11:34,547 --> 00:11:35,675
Right...

201
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:40,400
A long-distance relationship is not for everyone.

202
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:43,500
But I thought you guys could make it work.

203
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,844
Me, too.

204
00:11:44,844 --> 00:11:49,617
I really thought you guys could overcome the long distance.

205
00:11:49,617 --> 00:11:55,131
In the end, overcoming is just enduring all the pain.

206
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:57,900
And there is a limit to enduring.

207
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:02,300
What am I going to do about you, Yeon Du?

208
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,100
I'm fine.

209
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:08,100
Yesterday was a bit tough,

210
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,900
but I'm feeling better today.

211
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,266
That's why you went to the welcome party.

212
00:12:13,266 --> 00:12:16,165
So you could drink your pain away.

213
00:12:16,165 --> 00:12:18,189
Yes.

214
00:12:18,189 --> 00:12:21,500
Then I got wasted.

215
00:12:26,692 --> 00:12:28,600
What's wrong?

216
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:31,300
What? All of a sudden?

217
00:12:33,724 --> 00:12:35,771
Why are you going through my phone?

218
00:12:35,771 --> 00:12:37,616
Hey, what is your passcode?

219
00:12:37,616 --> 00:12:39,200
What is going on?

220
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,622
You said you got wasted yesterday.

221
00:12:41,622 --> 00:12:44,294
- So?
- Getting wasted after breakup...

222
00:12:44,294 --> 00:12:46,295
...equals a catastrophe.

223
00:12:46,295 --> 00:12:47,375
A catastrophe?

224
00:12:47,375 --> 00:12:48,300
"Are you asleep?"

225
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,600
Dot, dot, dot.

226
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,800
Equation mark?

227
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,500
[Chatrooms]

228
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:03,800
[Hyeon Ho: I'll be there soon. Just wait a little bit.]

229
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,000
- There was nothing?
- Are you okay?

230
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,500
- Are you really okay?
- Yes.

231
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:11,680
Fortunately, I didn't do such a thing.

232
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,000
That's good.

233
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:21,000
Kim Yeon Du, are you sure you're okay?

234
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,800
Yes, I'm okay.

235
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:29,600
There aren't that many couples that can make long-distance work.

236
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:33,300
Most people break up for similar reasons.

237
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:37,400
It's not because there was a problem or someone made a big mistake.

238
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:42,400
So you don't have to feel so guilty.

239
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:45,800
Okay. Thank you, Seol.

240
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:50,500
A senior is looking for me so I'm going to take off.

241
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:53,070
Okay, see you later.

242
00:13:59,056 --> 00:14:02,900
Do people break up for similar reasons?

243
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:07,800
Actually, that's not the reason Hyeon Ho and I broke up.

244
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,500
How are you going to pay for this?

245
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,200
I'm going to chase you until the end!

246
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,300
Kim Yeon Du!

247
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:15,000
Yeon Du.

248
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,750
- Hyeon Ho.
- Let me go!

249
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,900
I'm okay.

250
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:24,250
I'll be okay.

251
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:38,700
I'm sorry.

252
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:41,700
- Thank you.
- What?

253
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:42,912
Excuse me.

254
00:14:42,912 --> 00:14:44,500
Yes?

255
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,344
Are you all right?

256
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,500
Yes! I didn't even bump into you that hard.

257
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,100
No, not that.

258
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,800
Pardon?

259
00:14:54,012 --> 00:14:56,912
I see you're not all right.

260
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:00,200
No, I'm really okay.

261
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,000
I don't think so...

262
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,352
I mean, what are you...

263
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:07,900
Forget it.

264
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:10,000
Thanks anyway.

265
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,580
Kim Yeon Du?

266
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,800
What the...

267
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,570
He didn't follow me here, right?

268
00:15:58,947 --> 00:16:01,047
You scared me!

269
00:16:01,047 --> 00:16:02,900
Are you okay?

270
00:16:04,363 --> 00:16:06,000
Excuse me.

271
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,400
- This...
- I said, I'm really okay.

272
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,300
Pardon?

273
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:12,692
I told you I was okay, so why would you keep...

274
00:16:12,692 --> 00:16:13,700
Ah, really.

275
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,400
Why does he keep following me?

276
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,200
Your student ID...

277
00:16:25,802 --> 00:16:30,080
[We've finished dry cleaning your shirt. Please pick it up]

278
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:35,400
Da On, do you have time after class?

279
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,300
I have a favor to ask.

280
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,900
Oh, I'm so sorry,

281
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:42,900
but I already have plans after class.

282
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:45,200
But I'll definitely help you next time.

283
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,700
- Okay.
- But!

284
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:50,000
I'll hand this out for you.

285
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,662
Sure.

286
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,663
- Oh?
- You can just pass that along.

287
00:17:00,663 --> 00:17:02,900
- Ji Seong?
- Sorry?

288
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:05,200
You are a spitting image of my friend...

289
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,300
Nothing.

290
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,300
I'm sorry.

291
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,200
It's fine.

292
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:17,100
Ji Seong, there is someone in my school who looks just like you.

293
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:20,500
Ji Seong is studying at an academy now. What are you talking about?

294
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:23,000
And Ji Seong is way cooler!

295
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,143
Well then, I'll start by calling attendance.

296
00:17:26,143 --> 00:17:29,211
- Economics major Gu Jeong Ah.
- Here.

297
00:17:29,211 --> 00:17:31,922
- Economics major Shin Da On.
- Here.

298
00:17:31,922 --> 00:17:35,453
- Business major Kim Yeon Du.
- Here!

299
00:17:35,453 --> 00:17:38,060
Business major Do Ye Seok.

300
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:40,100
Do Ye Seok?

301
00:17:40,789 --> 00:17:44,200
Business major sophomore, Do Ye Seok?

302
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,100
Sophomore?

303
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:49,231
There is no one named Do Ye Seok among the seniors from what I know.

304
00:17:49,231 --> 00:17:50,853
If you're not here, I'll mark you absent.

305
00:17:50,853 --> 00:17:52,741
I'm here!

306
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,100
Wait, we have the same major?

307
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:06,100
Gosh... This is terrible.

308
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,000
What's going on?

309
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,620
Why is he coming this way?

310
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,800
Wait.

311
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,200
That shirt...

312
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:29,390
It looks familiar...

313
00:18:37,952 --> 00:18:39,852
Are you okay?

314
00:18:43,636 --> 00:18:45,536
Who the heck are you?

315
00:18:45,536 --> 00:18:47,400
That's enough.

316
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,600
She already apologized.

317
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:51,700
You guys are being pathetic.

318
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,800
You punk!

319
00:18:55,870 --> 00:18:58,190
Wait, wait.

320
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,300
Get lost.

321
00:19:09,528 --> 00:19:11,333
Are you asleep?

322
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,800
Are you asleep?

323
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,400
I asked you if you were sleeping!

324
00:19:17,512 --> 00:19:20,775
Kim Yeon Du, are you drunk?

325
00:19:20,775 --> 00:19:22,800
No.

326
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,085
I'm not drunk.

327
00:19:25,085 --> 00:19:27,896
I'm not drunk at all.

328
00:19:27,896 --> 00:19:29,800
Where are you? I'll come to find you.

329
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,567
Where am I?

330
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:33,600
I'm...

331
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,728
at the pub across from my school!

332
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,000
What the...

333
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:47,800
Hey. Get a hold of yourself.

334
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,500
Hey.

335
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,400
Ji Hyeon Ho?

336
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,488
Sorry?

337
00:19:55,488 --> 00:19:57,500
Hyeon Ho, did you really come?

338
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,500
Ji Hyeon Ho?

339
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,900
You shouldn't have come.

340
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,600
We broke up today.

341
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,200
It's over between us!

342
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,100
But...

343
00:20:10,019 --> 00:20:14,419
If you come to find me like this,

344
00:20:14,419 --> 00:20:17,720
then I won't be able to forget you!

345
00:20:22,976 --> 00:20:24,376
Hey.

346
00:20:24,376 --> 00:20:26,196
Excuse me!

347
00:20:26,196 --> 00:20:29,290
This is clearly a misunderstanding.

348
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:32,370
What's going on?

349
00:20:32,370 --> 00:20:34,780
Don't mind someone else's business.

350
00:20:34,780 --> 00:20:36,900
Keep going.

351
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,871
If... If you cry like this,

352
00:20:42,871 --> 00:20:45,296
you're putting me in a very awkward position.

353
00:20:45,296 --> 00:20:48,400
So calm down and...

354
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,100
Go back!

355
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:56,402
I'm here for my department's welcome party.

356
00:20:56,402 --> 00:20:59,900
People are waiting for me over there.

357
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:02,700
I'm really popular.

358
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,400
So go back!

359
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,140
I said go back!

360
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,600
What the...

361
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,400
What's wrong with her this time?

362
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,400
Hey.

363
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,598
Hello?

364
00:21:24,598 --> 00:21:26,100
I feel like I'm going to throw up.

365
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:28,500
What? Throw up?

366
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:29,300
No, wait!

367
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:31,500
This is my favorite...

368
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:33,300
This...

369
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,900
This is my favorite shirt.

370
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:53,300
You've got puke on your shirt.

371
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,900
Kim Yeon Du!

372
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,400
Who are you?

373
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,200
What were you going to do to my girlfriend?

374
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,000
Well?

375
00:22:29,168 --> 00:22:30,968
So it's you?

376
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,800
Her boyfriend?

377
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,100
[Best Mistake]

378
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:50,700
[Bonus clip]

379
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:52,849
Oh? How can I help you?

380
00:22:52,849 --> 00:22:54,300
I'm here to grab the application form

381
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,199
for the working student scholarship at the library.

382
00:22:56,224 --> 00:22:57,900
Oh, that.

383
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,666
Wait a second.

384
00:22:59,666 --> 00:23:02,600
Let's see.

385
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,800
Where is that?

386
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:09,600
Hello.

387
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,292
I'm trying to return to school.

388
00:23:11,292 --> 00:23:13,500
I'm a sophomore, Jin Sae Hui, majoring in Business Administration.

389
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,600
- Jin Se Hui?
- Oh, American style!

390
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,800
- Wow, even her name is pretty.
- Wait a second.

391
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,400
I saw it somewhere here.

392
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,400
[Next episode]
Exactly, why did we break up?

393
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,700
Should there be a special reason for breaking up?

394
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,500
If possible, don't be alone.

395
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:49,100
Speaking of which, do you want to go now?

396
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:49,900
Even.

397
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:51,200
"My Yeon Du?"

398
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,400
How dare he call her "my Yeon Du?"

399
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,200
Do you want to be friends?

400
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,370
What?

401
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:01,100
♫ Sometimes, I feel like I've filled it alone ♫

402
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:03,600
♫ So it makes me sad but... ♫

403
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:07,000
[Best Mistake]
